  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6584 sitting between the massive negative gamma wall at 6500 (-4.5B) and positive gamma at 6600 (+3.9B), dealers are currently in neutral hedging mode but poised for significant action. The PIN regime suggests dealers will sell any push toward 6600 resistance and aggressively buy any test of the 6500 support level, creating a tight trading range. The gex_surge event combined with extreme volatility in GEX readings (56% up 1-min, -53% down 5-min) indicates heavy options flow is reshaping the hedging landscape in real-time.\n\nKey strikes: 6500 downside magnet where dealers become forced buyers, 6600 upside resistance where dealers turn sellers, and 6775 flip level where regime changes to negative gamma if breached.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect heavy chop between 6500-6600 with dealers defending both levels aggressively.",
